cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 255 mi SSE of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to turn WNW, cross or graze the Yucatan Peninsula late Monday and then move into the south-central Gulf of Mexico Tuesday, eventually tracking toward the U.S. Gulf Coast mid-week.

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch in effect for Pinar del Rio, western Cuba
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Western Cuba, Yucatan Peninsula, U.S. Gulf Coast from Louisiana eastward to NW Florida (based on cone)
